snippet.textDisplay: FACTS ugghh what we call “covid-19” is just a buzzword for SARS (CoV-2). SARS-CoV-2 (or just SARS itself) because let’s face it, this current version of sars is merely a stronger version than the one seen in 2002/2003, it basically went to the gym for a couple of years and came back. Referring to the virus as its classification as the mainstream media and masses do is dangerous, especially with the fact that scarily, the population didn’t even know about the virus classification of ‘coronaviruses’ which have been around for about 20 years. i’ve been referring to this specific virus as SARS and i always will
